erful prison gang in the United States: the Mexican Mafia, or La Eme. These men granted Contreras unique access to their experiences, revealing how family members shun them, how jail and prison worsen them, how the church and drug treatment redeem them, and how their brightest moments lie in their pasts as legends of the California gang world. The Marvelous Ones gives human faces to the suffering and resilience of some of the most marginalized members of our society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDrug abusezCaliforniazEast Los Angeles. 0aMexican American gangszCaliforniazEast Los Angeles. 0aPrison gangszCaliforniazEast Los Angeles. 0aViolencezCaliforniazEast Los Angeles. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Caribbean & Latin American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520967977?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967977423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520967977/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles